definition: to spill/to overflow (of water, crowds)/to crowd (into a space)
to go forward/to advance/to go in/to enter/to put in/to submit/to take in/to admit/(math.) base of a number system/classifier for sections in a building or residential compound

sentences.english: People poured into the Beijing International Sculpture Park.
sentences.chinese: 人们涌进了北京国际雕塑公园。

sentences.english: Crowds poured in all the morning.
sentences.chinese: 整个上午，人们不断涌进来。

sentences.english: Once again, huge numbers packed Tahrir Square.
sentences.chinese: 大量示威者再次涌进了解放广场。

sentences.english: Mud surrounds several of the buildings near the river’s edge and branches into adjacent streets.
sentences.chinese: 淤泥包围了沿河的建筑，并涌进临近的街巷。

sentences.english: Water came up to his window and into his house.
sentences.chinese: 水上升到了他的窗口，涌进他的的房子。

sentences.english: After Chongqing opened the port, "modern agitation " poured into Sichuan Basin along the course of the Changjiang River.
sentences.chinese: 重庆开埠后，“近代风潮”沿长江航线涌进四川盆地。

sentences.english: They rarely talked about the hideous images that occasionally flooded their minds.
sentences.chinese: 他们几乎不谈那些偶尔会涌进脑海里的可怕画面。

sentences.english: Water poured in through a leak in the ship's hull.
sentences.chinese: 水从船体上的漏洞中涌进来。

sentences.english: The whole town was alive with talk about revolutionaries who were flooding the mills with their handbills.
sentences.chinese: 传说革命者涌进工厂里散发传单，这事弄得满城风雨。

sentences.english: Mary, missing melts into a thousand streams deluging into my world.
sentences.chinese: 玛丽，想念融化成一千条河流涌进我的世界。

sentences.english: Wave on wave of the audience entered into the theatre.
sentences.chinese: 一批又一批的观众涌进了剧场。

sentences.english: In the upside-down cabin, water spouted through the hatch.
sentences.chinese: 水哗哗地从舱口涌进翻倒的船舱。

sentences.english: So water rushes in, and the membrane expands.
sentences.chinese: 所以水会涌进去，膜扩张。

sentences.english: The sour vapour pours into the flourishing flour factory.
sentences.chinese: 酸蒸汽涌进兴旺的面粉厂。

sentences.english: A flood of Chinese products keep coming into the country.
sentences.chinese: 大量的中国产品不断涌进了这个国家。

sentences.english: There were wild celebrations as they streamed in through the gates.
sentences.chinese: 在他们涌进官邸大门的时候进行了疯狂的庆祝。

definition: to gush/to gush out/to pour out
to surge up violently (of ocean, river, lake etc)/turbulent
crowded to bursting point/filled to overflowing/jam-packed
to emerge in large numbers/to spring up/to emerge prominently
